  "why": "The paper’s coverage-guided fuzzer (CGT) uses metamorphic, domain-specific transformations (e.g., image translations/brightness/rotation; audio augmentation) and explicitly sets conservative per-mutation parameters so that individual mutations are slight and intended to preserve semantics and naturalness. However, the fuzzer iteratively adds successful mutants back into the seed queue and continues mutating them (Algorithm 2), and the paper does not describe any mechanism that enforces semantic equivalence relative to the original seed or that bounds cumulative distortion across iterations. Thus semantic consistency and naturalness are enforced at the per-mutation (successive-step) level but the design does not prevent gradual drift across multiple mutation rounds.",
